BagItProfile_acceptBagItVersion_help: Which version or versions of the BagIt specification does this profile support?
BagItProfile_acceptSerialization_help: Can bags conforming to this profile be seriazed in formats like zip, tar, etc.?
BagItProfile_allowFetchTxt_help: Are fetch.txt files allowed? These files contain URLs of files that should be part of the bag. DART does not yet support packaging or validating fetch.txt files.
BagItProfile_allowMiscDirectories_help: Can the bag contain directories other than 'data' in the top-level directory?
BagItProfile_allowMiscTopLevelFiles_help: Can the bag contain files in the top-level directory other than manifests, tag manifests, and standard tag files like bagit.txt and bag-info.txt?
BagItProfile_manifestsRequired_help: Which manifests must be present in the bag? The BagIt specification says there must be at least one.
BagItProfile_name_help: A meaningful name to distinguish this profile from others. For example, 'APTrust with library pre-set default values'.
BagItProfile_tagManifestsRequired_help: Which tag manifests must be present in the bag? The BagIt specifications allows for zero or more.
BagItProfile_tarDirMustMatchName_help: When expanding a tarred or zipped bag, must the directory name match that zip/tar file name? If yes, then my_bag.tar, my_bag.zip, etc. must expand to a folder called my_bag.
RemoteRepository_apiToken_help: Enter the API key or token that allows you to access this repository.
RemoteRepository_loginExtra_help: Extra information required to establish or configure the connection to the remote repository. This is not necessary for most repositories.
RemoteRepository_name_help: The name of the remote remote repository. For repos that offer both test and production environments, the name should indicate which environment you'll be connecting to.
RemoteRepository_pluginId_help: Choose the plugin that provides access to this repository.
RemoteRepository_url_help: This should typically be the URL of the remote repository's REST API.
RemoteRepository_userId_help: The User Id required to connect to the remote repository. Some repositories that use API keys do not require this.
UploadTarget_bucket_help: The name of the bucket or default folder into which items should be uploaded.
UploadTarget_host_help: The host name or IP address of the upload target. For example, 's3.amazonaws.com', 'ftp.example.com', '10.10.0.1'
UploadTarget_loginExtra_help: Leave this blank unless otherwise instructed.
UploadTarget_login_help: The login name or email address used to connect to the remote server. For S3 connections, this can be an AWS access key ID.
UploadTarget_name_help: The name of the service you'll be uploading to. For services that offer both test and production environments, you should specify which environment you're targeting. For example, 'APTrust Test', 'APTrust Production', etc.
UploadTarget_password_help: The password used to connect to the remote server. For S3 connections, this can be the AWS secret access key.
UploadTarget_port_help: The port to connect to on the remote server. If you're not sure, enter zero, and DART will use the service's default port.
UploadTarget_protocol_help: The network protocol used to upload items to the target.
baseProfile_empty_label: None - I want to build a new profile from scratch
BagItProfile_serialization_help: Must bags conforming to this profile be serialized (e.g. in tar or zip format)? Or is serialization optional or forbidden?
BagItProfile_infoIdentifier_help: A URL that identifies this profile. Ideally, a copy of the profile is available at this URL.
BagItProfile_infoContactEmail_help: The email address of the person who maintains this profile.
BagItProfile_infoContactName_help: The name of the person who maintains this profile.
BagItProfile_infoSourceOrganization_help: The name of the organization that maintains this profile.
TagDefinition_required_help: Is this tag required to be present?
TagDefinition_emptyOk_help: Is it OK for this tag to be present but have an empty value?
TagDefinition_values_help: If this tag has a limited set of allowed values, enter them here, one value per line.
TagDefinition_isBuiltIn_help: Is this a built-in tag that should never be deleted from the profile?
TagDefinition_help_help: Describe the meaning of this tag.

JobPackageOp_packageFormat_help: How should the job package these files?
JobPackageOp_bagItProfileId_help: Which BagIt Profile should this job use. When creating the bag, DART will ensure the bag adheres to this profile, and will automatically copy in this profile's default values.
JobPackageOp_outputPath_help: Where should this job put local copies of the files it creates?
JobPackageOp_packageName_help: This should be the file or bag name of the package you are creating. For example, 'my_bag', 'PhotoCollection_1234', etc. This will become part of the file name, so avoid spaces and special punctuation characters.
